      • getPreferenceRank

        public int getPreferenceRank()
        Getter for preferenceRank, or how much a student wants to take a class. The lower the number, the more the student wants to take the class. Lowest number allowed is 0.
        Returns:
        int represneting how much student wants to take the class.

      • setPreferenceRank

        public void setPreferenceRank​(int preferenceRank)
        Setter for preferenceDao rank, or how much a student wants to take a class. The lower the int, the more the student wants to take the class. Lowest number allowed is 0, and no duplicates allowed (i.e. student cannot have 2 classes with preferenceRank of 2. It is assumed that this is handled at a higher level.
        Parameters:
        preferenceRank - int reprensenting the preferenceRank
